    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# The DID estimate suggests a positive effect (+379), but it is not statistically significant (p > 0.05), and the confidence interval includes zero.\n",
        "# Additionally, the parallel trends assumption is violated, as treated and control groups exhibit very different pre-treatment trends.\n",
        "# EconML results consistently show a negative ATE (-150 to -280), indicating that the campaign may have reduced sales.\n",
        "# Therefore, the causal impact of the campaign is uncertain, and more reliable methods (ML-based) suggest a negative effect.\n",
